title: Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks
text:
The Canadian Press - ONLINE EDITION Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks By: The Associated Press Report Error 
The following list represents the most streamed tracks on Spotify, based on the number of people who shared it divided by the number who listened to it, from Friday, Oct. 2 to Thursday, Oct. 8 via Facebook, Tumblr, Twitter and Spotify. 
CANADA 
1. Justin Bieber, "What Do You Mean?" (Def Jam Recordings) 
2. Drake, "Hotline Bling" (Cash Money Records Inc.) 
3. The Weeknd, "Can't Feel My Face" (Republic Records) 
4. The Weeknd, "The Hills" (Republic Records) 
5. Major Lazer & DJ Snake featuring MO, "Lean On" (Mad Decent) 
6. R. City featuring Adam Levine, "Locked Away" (Kemosabe Records) 
7. Drake and Future, "Jumpman" (Cash Money Records Inc.) 
8. Ellie Goulding, "On My Mind" (Polydor Ltd.) 
9. Robin Schulz featuring Francesco Yates, "Sugar" (Warner Music Group Germany Holding GmbH) 
10. Shawn Mendes, "Stitches" (Island Records)
